reviews.review_text: Perfection I love how after 44 years you are still searching for that perfect sound. Your work is much appreciated. Long live the Grateful Dead!!!

Hunter's Found the Secret Sauce All of us have long been grateful to Hunter and others for the efforts they expend to improve the GD experience of countless peoples. Maybe others have noticed as I have, that lately Hunter's offerings have achieved a new level of excellence. This is a 10 star upgrade. I'm blown away. Especially because this has always been a super hot show that has collectively got about 20 reviews, because none of the sources did any justice to it. You really had to listen and use your imagination to hear how great they were this night. Well not anymore. This is the 3re review I've left specifically because I was so overjoyed to find such a beautiful new source.

This is quintessential fall 79. as well as fun and unique.

Check out that 1st set. Cold Rain opener, Dancing> Franklins mid-set. Oh and the Dancing, uh yea, and the Franklin's holy balls. Also excellent Peggy-O, Jed too. A short but wild Deal. 

Finally getting to hear Scarlet in all its glory and it is instantly a new favorite. Fire is top marks too. Jebus crap the Truckin' is crazy time awesome. Tell me the peak doesn't remind you of 10/27/79 Other One. This show is just popping with energy and inspired play, and now a strong version for the ears.
